1
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:42,879
Finally found it!

2
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:43,479
Let's go.

3
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:44,839
Walk.

4
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:45,759
Stop right there.

5
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,199
Wait—there's someone here?

6
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:54,079
Did you all miss him?

7
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:00,759
Put the deed down—

8
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,439
and I'll let you go.

9
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:15,479
I will not.

10
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,879
I'll just walk right out of here.

11
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,919
Try and stop me.

12
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:32,559
You bunch of villains!

13
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:34,559
Put it down now!

14
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,559
You lot—

15
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,239
what a curious bunch you all are.

16
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,519
Think you can all just die?

17
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:49,479
If you want to leave—

18
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:52,079
you'll have to ask this broom of mine

19
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,039
if it agrees.

20
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,959
Get over here!

21
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,519
You old man!

22
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,719
Run? I'll chase!

23
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:10,519
Wait—

24
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,959
Now I've got you!

25
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,599
Are you all right?

26
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,439
Not exactly.

27
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,119
You dare hit me?

28
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,399
Old man, I'll hit you again.

29
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:44,559
I'll teach you to cause trouble!

30
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:45,679
Watch out—brawling!

31
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,479
Find somewhere to hide!

32
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,199
You old fool!

33
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,679
I'll teach you!

34
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,359
Changyu!

35
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,919
Changyu! Changyu, quick!

36
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,159
Aunt Zhuang!

37
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,119
Watch Ning'er for me.

38
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:24,359
Go!

39
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,599
Get out!

40
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,479
Miss Fan!

41
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,359
Listen to me—

42
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,759
I see who dares interfere!

43
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,359
Run! Run!

44
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,279
Changyu!

45
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,999
Stop! Stop fighting!

46
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:19,518
Old Zhao has half killed them.

47
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,759
If you hit them again, someone will die.

48
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,119
Still haven't learned?

49
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,199
Miss Fan!

50
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,199
Miss Fan!

51
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,559
Miss Fan!

52
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:32,359
Don't misunderstand.

53
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,919
We came this time

54
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,279
to congratulate you on your wedding.

55
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:37,399
That's right—congratulations!

56
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:37,999
We came to offer our blessings.

57
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,479
We never came for the deed.

58
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,959
Coming with weapons to offer blessings?

59
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,279
My husband is already injured,

60
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,439
and you attacked him on top of that.

61
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,119
No no—we didn't!

62
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,439
We never touched him!

63
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,639
Not a hair on him!

64
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,199
He scared himself.

65
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,119
He got scared—that's all.

66
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,039
We didn't touch him.

67
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,599
Getting scared doesn't count?

68
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,799
This must be the esteemed groom!

69
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,159
We failed to recognize a man of your stature.

70
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,159
Here, take some money—

71
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,959
some money for you.

72
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,359
We really did come to congratulate you.

73
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,879
Please spare us.

74
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:24,719
Get out of here.

75
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,599
Now.

76
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,439
Go! Run!

77
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,599
Well done! Well done! Well done!

78
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,879
Are you all right?

79
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,279
They did hurt you.

80
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,159
Let me go deal with them.

81
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,919
Don't blame them.

82
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,159
Then who?

83
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:47,439
Blame me.

84
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,479
I was sitting nearby.

85
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,799
It's partly my fault.

86
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,239
It's on me.

87
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,159
All right then—

88
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,119
watch your step! Careful!

89
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,279
Clumsy old man.

90
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,679
I only went out to buy vegetables,

91
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,599
and look at the state of things.

92
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:08,919
Thanks to Uncle for stepping in.

93
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,919
I can't thank you enough.

94
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,799
Aunt Zhao, you go rest.

95
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,079
Let me look after Yan Zheng.

96
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,719
All right.

97
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,359
I'll cook something for everyone.

98
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,559
Go, go, go!

99
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,919
Go on out.

100
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,279
Yan Zheng, give me your hand.

101
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,199
Old Zhao—come out here.

102
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,519
What is it?

103
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:31,079
What do you mean? Come here.

104
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:31,759
I haven't taken his pulse yet.

105
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,399
What pulse?

106
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,359
No sense of the moment.

107
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,559
No sense of the moment?

108
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,719
The wound on his back has torn open.

109
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,119
A large bloodstain.

110
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,079
I need to clean it.

111
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,119
I can do it myself.

112
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,439
Let me.

113
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,039
You caused this—it's only fair.

114
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,159
These wounds—

115
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:06,759
even from being sat on,

116
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,719
they shouldn't have torn this badly.

117
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:09,559
You must have been fighting.

118
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,679
Your build—

119
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,159
I can tell you know martial arts.

120
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,079
I was an escort guard.

121
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,799
Traveling the roads,

122
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,279
I learned some moves for protection.

123
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,719
I wasn't trying to hide it.

124
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,439
I understand.

125
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:39,679
My father was also an escort guard.

126
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,159
He had scars just like yours.

127
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,199
Escort work—

128
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,719
truly a life gambled with one's own body.

129
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:01,039
Hold still.

130
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,479
He was attacked by bandits

131
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,279
at Tiger's Fork Pass.

132
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,879
That's why he was hurt.

133
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,039
I see.

134
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,599
There's nothing valuable in the house.

135
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,399
They could have taken what they wanted.

136
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,319
So why did you fight back?

137
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,599
I would not let them take this.

138
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:29,679
You fought for the deed?

139
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,079
Thank you.

140
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:40,119
That one swing of my broom—

141
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,918
everyone went down.

142
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,158
I'm telling you—

143
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,759
back a cornered rabbit against a wall

144
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,039
and it'll bite.

145
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,839
If not for this fight,

146
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,159
I'd never have known I had it in me.

147
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,159
Ha! Indeed.

148
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:31,559
We're the warriors of West Lane.

149
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,039
That we are.

150
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:36,159
Have a drink!

151
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,999
Drink!

152
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,999
We're no worse than Marquis Wu'an!

153
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:40,959
Right?

154
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,359
Mind you,

155
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,319
you're looking a bit weak.

156
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:44,439
Let Old Zhao sit on you and down you go.

157
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:46,519
Changyu had better fatten you up.

158
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,959
His old wounds haven't healed.

159
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,519
Come on—have a drink with me!

160
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,239
Drink!

161
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:56,519
You can't drink with that wound.

162
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,239
He can drink—it helps blood flow.

163
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,359
Old Zhao!

164
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,239
Stop stirring things up.

165
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,679
Fresh wound—no alcohol.

166
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,599
Just because you like to be different.

167
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,919
Go sit over there.

168
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,679
Old Zhao! Come have a drink!

169
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:23,119
Let's drink!

170
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:23,799
Changyu—Fan Da really filed that complaint?

171
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,759
He's that shameless?

172
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:28,799
Should we hire a lawyer?

173
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,039
A lawyer would cost a lot.

174
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,919
What then?

175
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,439
What about Song Yan?

176
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,319
He's the only scholar in West Lane.

177
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:34,999
A licentiate doesn't have to kneel before officials.

178
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,239
He could surely help Changyu.

179
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,159
Big sister won't go to bad people for help.

180
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:40,159
Ning'er is right.

181
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,159
Right. Let's not mention that ingrate.

182
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,959
Come on, drink!

183
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,679
Here's to our brothers!

184
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,839
Drink!

185
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,439
Here.

186
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,959
Let me help you.

187
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:00,759
Just these.

188
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,079
My mother's things.

189
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,719
They'll have to do.

190
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,919
I've written out the court procedure

191
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:11,159
and the relevant laws.

192
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,839
Memorize them.

193
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,159
You can get through the hearing.

194
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,319
You know how to write?

195
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:15,799
And you know the law?

196
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,319
I've traveled widely.

197
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,359
You pick things up.

198
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:32,359
What's wrong?

199
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,919
I used to think

200
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,079
Song Yan was the most capable man in the world.

201
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,479
But you're even better.

202
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,079
Not only do you know martial arts,

203
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,679
you can write too.

204
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:44,519
Unlike that man—

205
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,519
the one Aunt Zhao called herself hoarse trying to get

206
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,879
who wouldn't even come out to help.

207
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,799
Would you argue the case for me?

208
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,119
By Da Yin law,

209
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,039
only the head of household may appear in court.

210
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,759
I am not the head of household.

211
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,959
I cannot appear in court.

212
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,999
Then I'm the one being thrown in.

213
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,639
My turn.

214
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:16,919
Order in the court!

215
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,319
Who are you and what is this case?

216
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:23,239
State your business.

217
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,799
You're so imposing.

218
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:29,599
I respectfully address Your Honor—

219
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,039
I am the commoner Fan Changyu.

220
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,439
I bring this case about—

221
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:35,639
a house.

222
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:36,759
Are your parents living?

223
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:40,039
Both deceased.

224
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,239
According to Da Yin law,

225
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,639
when a household has no male heir,

226
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:48,919
the property passes to the nearest male kin.

227
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:50,599
If an elder brother dies, the younger inherits.

228
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:54,399
If the younger dies—

229
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,879
Talking nonsense in my court!

230
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,199
Ning'er!

231
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:06,959
Silence!

232
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:08,199
The board!

233
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:09,799
You're serious?

234
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:10,799
I most respectfully address Your Honor.

235
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,439
According to Da Yin law,

236
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:13,839
Household Code, the Childless Household Article,

237
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:15,199
Number Seventeen—

238
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,199
the right to establish a successor—

239
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:19,519
Stop.

240
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:22,959
The right to establish a successor—

241
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:23,599
what does this mean?

242
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:25,359
Your Honor, I have trouble remembering written words,

243
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,359
so my mother taught me a rhyme

244
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:30,799
to help me remember.

245
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,679
I'm used to saying it that way—

246
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:38,319
I just can't help it.

247
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:41,479
Well then—

248
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,279
how about we find a sack

249
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,599
and tie Fan Da up?

250
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:44,959
Then what?

251
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,559
Uncle Wang said

252
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:47,839
if Fan Da isn't present at the hearing,

253
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,079
the case is void.

254
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,439
So once won't be enough.

255
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:54,839
There'll always be a next time.

256
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:55,999
Better to just—

257
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:00,439
kill him.

258
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:01,719
Get it over with.

259
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:03,959
Killing is against the law.

260
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,639
Better not.

261
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,079
If you can't be that ruthless,

262
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,319
then you'll just have to endure.

263
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:11,239
Keep memorizing.

264
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,679
[Advertisement]

265
