[Advertisement]

274
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,159
Da Yin law, Household Code—

275
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,199
[Advertisement]

276
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,239
[Advertisement]

277
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:58,919
[Advertisement]

278
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,519
[Advertisement]

279
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:02,559
[Advertisement]

280
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:04,159
[Advertisement]

281
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,159
[Advertisement]

282
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:10,119
[Advertisement]

283
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:11,559
[Advertisement]

284
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,439
Da Yin law, Household Code,

285
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,519
Article Seventeen—

286
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,838
For a household without heirs,

287
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,119
stop being angry.

288
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:32,759
Your health matters.

289
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,039
I'll keep memorizing.

290
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,079
Fine.

291
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,119
Try memorizing the Seven-Step Poem instead.

292
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,399
The law ultimately comes down to reason.

293
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:42,679
An appeal to emotion might move the magistrate.

294
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,519
Magistrate Cui was a two-time examination graduate, after all.

295
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,759
What is the Seven-Step Poem?

296
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:51,679
Boiling beans over burning beanstalk;

297
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:52,839
the beans weep in the cauldron.

298
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:54,399
Born of the same root—

299
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,759
why burn me so fiercely?

300
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:56,799
What does it mean?

301
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:59,719
Burning the beanstalk to cook the beans—

302
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:02,639
describing brothers in a deadly struggle.

303
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,879
A metaphor for Fan Da bullying his brother's daughter,

304
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:06,759
cruel and without feeling.

305
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:08,679
Brilliant!

306
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:14,199
It's as if this poem was written for Fan Da.

307
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,399
Though he's not worthy of it.

308
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,319
What does 'cauldron' mean?

309
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:26,159
Same root—is that about having the same father?

310
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,039
And 'why burn me fiercely'—

311
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,599
is that a cooking method?

312
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:33,919
It's a metaphor for killing.

313
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:41,039
I've got it!

314
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:48,959
Burning beans on blazing stalks—

315
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:50,919
the beans

316
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:53,839
holler from the pot.

317
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:57,359
Same father gave us both life—

318
00:18:57,360 --> 00:19:00,239
why am I killed first?

319
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,159
That's not quite right—

320
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,439
but not entirely wrong either.

321
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:18,079
Your Honor!

322
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,719
Burning beans on blazing stalks—

323
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:26,999
the beans holler from the pot.

324
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:29,719
Same father gave us both life—

325
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:32,319
why am I killed first?

326
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,559
Burning beans on blazing stalks—

327
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:50,159
the beans holler from the pot.

328
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:53,039
Same father gave us both life—

329
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:56,639
why am I killed first?

330
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:09,639
Your Honor!

331
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,119
Where is young Song going?

332
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,199
Son is just taking a stroll, mother.

333
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:26,439
He's been reading too long.

334
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:38,079
You still have the provincial exam,

335
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,279
and then the palace exam.

336
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,879
Don't get distracted.

337
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:48,839
Yes.

338
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,519
Boiling beans...

339
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:59,319
Mother.

340
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:02,799
I'm so tired.

341
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,599
Did I disturb you?

342
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,159
I just fell asleep with my head on your hand.

343
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:02,999
I understand—you're tired from reading too.

344
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,439
I completely understand.

345
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:11,759
Why is the lamp out?

346
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:12,839
I'll find a tinderbox.

347
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:17,559
Who knocks at this hour?

348
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,079
Song Yan.

349
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,079
Why have you come?

350
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:25,879
Let me in first.

351
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:27,159
Don't let my mother see.

352
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:29,159
I have something—

353
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:31,679
Something for you.

354
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,439
Changyu,

355
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,119
I came here at great risk—

356
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:44,479
defying my mother's express wishes—

357
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:45,559
to help you keep this home.

358
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:47,599
What?

359
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:49,479
These past days,

360
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,519
I've been thinking hard.

361
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,919
I finally found a solution.

362
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,319
I am here to tell you—

363
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,399
I am willing to take you as a concubine.

364
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,239
Have you been kicked in the head by a donkey?

365
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,559
Don't get excited—

366
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,639
I can only try to ask the magistrate

367
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:09,559
for a special exception.

368
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,639
But with my licentiate status,

369
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,639
he may grant me a favor.

370
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,279
That way you keep your home

371
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:17,919
and gain a proper status.

372
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,319
Song Yan.

373
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,999
You think that I—a pig butcher—

374
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:26,359
should be grateful

375
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,639
that you'd lower yourself to take me as a concubine?

376
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,199
I never meant it that way.

377
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:32,359
I simply didn't expect you

378
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:34,039
to be so rash about this house—

379
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:35,879
to give yourself to a crippled drifter from Chongzhou.

380
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,359
A crippled drifter.

381
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,559
Is that so.

382
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:40,559
So.

383
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,479
Song Yan, I'm genuinely curious—

384
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,599
what gives you the right to look down on him?

385
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,759
Never mind that Yan Zheng is accomplished and learned,

386
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:50,599
well-read and well-mannered—

387
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:51,399
in looks alone,

388
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,759
he outranks you ten to one.

389
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,159
More importantly,

390
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:56,039
he's grateful.

391
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:58,119
He understands my difficulties.

392
00:24:58,600 --> 00:24:59,799
He agreed to marry into my household.

393
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,199
When I was in danger,

394
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,839
even with his own injuries,

395
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:05,959
he stood up for me.

396
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:07,519
That kind of loyalty and devotion—

397
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:10,159
isn't that worth a thousand times what you offer?

398
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:14,159
You're just bitter right now.

399
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:17,199
You want to look good in front of the neighbors.

400
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,439
That's why you came here.

401
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:20,119
Song Yan,

402
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,159
you want it all, don't you?

403
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:24,439
Every good thing in the world.

404
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:25,559
That's not it.

405
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:27,239
I care for you sincerely.

406
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:28,959
I, Song Yan, take your hand tonight

407
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:29,999
and swear to Heaven—

408
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:33,319
I—

409
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,359
Who are you?

410
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:41,039
Who am I?

411
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,239
A crippled drifter.

412
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:54,759
I've been pining for you night and day,

413
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:57,479
yet you show so little virtue?

414
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:58,599
What are you to her, that she owes you virtue?

415
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,159
You two have no shame—

416
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:02,719
absolutely indecent!

417
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:04,279
Utterly disgraceful!

418
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,519
According to Da Yin law,

419
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:07,119
illicit relations are punishable by eighty lashes!

420
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:08,479
According to Da Yin law,

421
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,679
breaking into a private home at night is treated as theft!

422
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,159
Beat him to death—he'd deserve it!

423
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:13,839
You see?

424
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,359
This is my husband.

425
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,839
Fan Changyu's lawfully wedded man.

426
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:28,279
You two—

427
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:31,679
how shameful!

428
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:35,319
Carrying on like this—it's an outrage!

429
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,599
Absolutely disgraceful.

430
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:57,479
As if I would kiss him.

431
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:00,879
If I scared him off from being my live-in husband,

432
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:05,079
I'd be getting the worst end of this deal.

433
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:31,959
Damn that Song Yan.

434
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:34,799
Damn him!

435
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,999
Damn him, damn him, damn him!

436
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,839
What on earth is that woman thinking?

437
00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:54,079
All this for a live-in husband?

438
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,519
Aunt, where's Uncle?

439
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:13,519
He went to town.

440
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:24,719
Uncle Zhao is back!

441
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:27,479
Aunt, I have to step out for a moment.

442
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:29,159
Changyu.

443
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:35,239
These two—

444
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,319
why do they keep avoiding each other?

445
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:40,719
Before the wedding, girls get nervous.

446
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:42,879
Even a tough girl like Changyu

447
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:44,279
gets shy.

448
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:46,999
Were you shy before you married me?

449
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:47,999
Shy?

450
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,159
I was in tears and couldn't find the right temple door.

451
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:51,959
Yan Zheng.

452
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,119
Yan Zheng, you're awake.

453
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:56,079
Changyu just went out.

454
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:56,919
I know.

455
00:28:57,920 --> 00:28:59,159
I need to speak with you, Uncle.

456
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:00,319
As it happens, I was looking for you too.

457
00:29:00,320 --> 00:29:01,079
Come here.

458
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:01,759
Come.

459
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:03,839
Careful.

460
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:08,199
This essay you wrote—

461
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,679
how much did it actually sell for?

462
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,079
Is twenty taels a lot?

463
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:15,239
Twenty taels and you're asking if it's a lot?

464
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:18,359
I thought the bookseller had gone mad.

465
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:23,399
Already at Lin'an's Four Seasons Bookshop.

466
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:25,839
What kind of writing was it?

467
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:30,719
I travel widely and have seen a lot.

468
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,799
I just wrote down what I observed.

469
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:34,479
I didn't expect

470
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:36,239
the bookseller to actually buy it.

471
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:39,559
That's practically printing money.

472
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,959
Write a few more—I'll sell them.

473
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:45,439
I imitate the styles of great scholars.

474
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:47,999
Too many and my imitation would show.

475
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:48,759
Not wise.

476
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:52,559
Right, right—shouldn't flaunt it.

477
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:54,959
But writing one now and then—

478
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:56,559
that's enough to last a year.

479
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,799
This little bit—enough for a year?

480
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:03,439
For a modest household,

481
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:05,519
managed carefully,

482
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:06,919
it'd last two or three years.

483
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:09,199
Seems I've not budgeted well enough.

484
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:12,719
Keep my essay selling a secret.

485
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,919
Don't tell anyone.

486
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:15,999
I understand.

487
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:16,599
I understand.

488
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:18,319
This old man can keep his mouth shut.

489
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:19,799
Won't go spreading it around.

490
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:23,079
This silly girl—

491
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:25,839
she found herself a husband who can earn money.

492
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:30,279
She's finally got some good fortune ahead.

493
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:50,079
Changyu!

494
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:51,159
Aunt.

495
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:53,199
You took forever—come see who's here!

496
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:55,479
Come look who's waiting for you!

497
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:57,119
Auntie Chen is here!

498
00:30:57,520 --> 00:30:58,639
Long Yu, dear.

499
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:01,839
Open it up.

500
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,239
Open it and see.

501
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:27,879
Mine!

502
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,319
But you said you were only making his.

503
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,359
Girls always come first.

504
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:37,359
I saved on the fabric

505
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:39,119
and borrowed a little from a neighbor.

506
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:39,679
So—

507
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:41,199
I made you one too.

508
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:42,839
Thank you.

509
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:43,959
Of course.

510
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,799
It's beautiful.

511
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:47,079
See—

512
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:49,239
so beautiful.

513
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,439
What is this?

514
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:02,599
Don't you like it?

515
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:06,279
I like it.

516
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:09,679
But with such beautiful embroidery—

517
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:10,639
who's going to see it?

518
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:13,439
It's not for you to see.

519
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,679
If your husband likes it, that's what matters.

520
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:18,999
But this is for him to wear.

521
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:23,559
Oh, you silly girl.

522
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:27,199
You wear this on your wedding night—for him to see.

523
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:33,199
Aunt!

524
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:34,359
All right, all right.

525
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:53,479
Boiling beans over burning beanstalk,

526
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:56,839
the beans weep quietly in the cauldron.

527
00:32:58,040 --> 00:32:59,999
Both from the same root—

528
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:02,679
why burn me so fiercely?

529
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:08,479
Boiling beans over burning beanstalk,

530
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:14,359
the beans weep loudly in the cauldron.

531
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:24,199
Oops—

532
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:26,399
the beanstalk shouldn't be hiding under the bed.

533
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:30,879
the beans weep loudly in the cauldron.

534
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:35,039
Both from the same root—

535
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:38,679
why burn me so fiercely?

536
00:33:45,120 --> 00:33:46,519
Why are you here?

537
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:51,199
Didn't you say yesterday to come try on the wedding clothes?

538
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:56,399
But our wedding clothes

539
00:33:57,120 --> 00:33:58,559
are at Aunt Zhao's place.

540
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:06,079
How did she end up sitting on the bed?

541
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:20,079
How did he end up sitting next to me?

542
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,999
Let's go try them on together.

543
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:30,039
Sure!

544
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:34,359
Let's go together.

545
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,439
Let's go.

546
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:45,479
Why isn't he leaving?

547
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:47,599
He couldn't have seen it—

548
00:34:48,639 --> 00:34:50,678
Where's the box? I can't find it.

549
00:34:52,120 --> 00:34:53,239
Have you finished memorizing? Done with your task?

550
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,638
Memorizing—

551
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:56,119
I—

552
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:58,119
Where was I?

553
00:34:58,120 --> 00:34:59,119
Both from the same father...

554
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:03,639
Born of the same root...

555
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:14,679
I'll go first.

556
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:23,399
She probably hasn't seen it.

557
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,159
I'll give it to her another day.

558
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:45,519
Probably didn't see it.

559
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:47,479
Definitely didn't see. Definitely not.

560
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,719
How mortifying.

561
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:53,839
What do I do?

562
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:22,919
What a lively scene!

563
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:26,759
Son, you're here for Changyu's happy wedding day.

564
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,719
Make sure you remember all the steps.

565
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:31,359
Don't worry—you know best.

566
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,159
But today you're the host.

567
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:35,039
You just enjoy your tea. I'll handle it.

568
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:44,679
I heard the live-in husband is quite ugly?

569
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:46,319
A cripple too?

570
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,559
Neither ugly nor crippled—

571
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:50,839
who'd be a live-in husband these days?

572
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:52,919
Matchmaker Kang—on such a happy day,

573
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:53,999
watch your mouth.

574
00:36:54,680 --> 00:36:55,559
She really talks too much.

575
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:56,959
Why is she here too?

576
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:59,479
A distant Fan family relative—can't be helped.

577
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:03,199
The groom leaving his family home—

578
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,119
what did I say?

579
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:14,719
See—not missing a single limb.

580
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:15,799
Who'd be a live-in husband these days?

581
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,599
I, Song Yan, late graduate, come to offer congratulations.

582
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:30,679
Why are you here again?

583
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,159
Ayu.

584
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:36,319
I'm giving you one last chance.

585
00:37:37,280 --> 00:37:38,599
If you consent to be my concubine,

586
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,679
I'll honor my original vow and take you in.

587
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:42,799
A concubine!

588
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:44,519
Is he not disgusting?

589
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:45,919
He's deliberately humiliating my big sister.

590
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:48,559
He's here to humiliate my big sister?

591
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:51,319
This jade figurine is a love token Ayu once gave me.

592
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:55,439
Now that we are only as siblings,

593
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:57,959
I should pass it to her husband.

594
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:00,599
I gave you that clay doll when I was six.

595
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:02,999
How is that a love token?

596
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:04,359
You still remember something from when you were six—

597
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:06,359
clearly you never got over it.

598
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:08,999
Don't make me slap you.

599
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:13,719
A groom receiving a gift—how rude not to accept.

600
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,559
Live-in husband of the Fan family—

601
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,279
will you accept or not?

602
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:21,159
That face—

603
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:03,199
no wonder Changyu says she hasn't lost anything.

604
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:05,639
Who was the blind person who earlier said

605
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:08,359
the groom was some kind of ugly scarecrow?

606
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:09,719
Who was that?

607
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,159
That'd be you, Matchmaker Kang.

608
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,839
In all my years of matchmaking,

609
00:39:15,640 --> 00:39:17,919
that face—never mind Song Yan being outclassed—

610
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:20,839
there's no one like that in all of Lin'an.

611
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,279
Not in the whole county.

612
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:24,199
I'm asking you—accept or not?

613
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:24,719
I—

614
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:29,799
accept.

615
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:31,119
Not accept—marry!

616
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:34,599
I meant accept the gift token—

617
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:42,279
not for them to get married!

618
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:44,039
Being too kind doesn't pay.

619
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:45,119
You raised that ungrateful creature.

620
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:46,359
Do you have anything else that might bite back?

621
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:53,919
I've raised many animals.

622
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,199
The only one that ever bit was that one.

623
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:58,479
Thank you.

624
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:03,119
Gold in your eyes—can't see jade.

625
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:05,159
Fan Changyu.

626
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:06,519
I'll forgive you for being blinded.

627
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:14,599
I'll ask you one final time:

628
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:16,679
do you or do you not—

629
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:19,679
You—

630
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:21,679
get out.

631
00:40:21,680 --> 00:40:22,599
Fine.

632
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:24,999
Listen carefully.

633
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:27,159
One day, when I pass the palace exam,

634
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:31,399
you'll regret this.

635
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:35,519
You!

636
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:38,079
Fan Changyu! Yan Zheng!

637
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:39,519
Don't think you've won.

638
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,359
When I pass the highest exam,

639
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:46,679
you'll have something coming.

640
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:49,919
Bow to the elders!

641
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:51,319
Bow!

642
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:52,959
Sharing of the sacred meal—

643
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:54,319
henceforth in joy and sorrow together,

644
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,599
never to part.

645
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:10,719
Sharing of the wedding wine—

646
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:22,279
the three-cup ritual.

647
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:25,319
With respect and courtesy between spouses.

648
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,679
Joined cup ritual—

649
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,159
wine mingled as one.

650
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:47,919
May husband and wife be forever united.

651
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:50,319
Well done!

652
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,399
Well done!

653
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:57,159
The couple bows to each other!

654
00:41:57,520 --> 00:42:00,079
The wedding is complete!

655
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:17,959
Well done!

656
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:21,759
Well done!

657
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:40,639
Well done!

658
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:46,839
Well done!

659
00:42:49,720 --> 00:42:52,559
By tradition, a live-in husband takes the wife's surname.

660
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:53,559
No need.

661
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:56,039
My husband keeps his own name.

662
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,199
Yan Zheng.

663
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:58,079
That suits him just fine.

664
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:01,239
As for the children—

665
00:43:01,680 --> 00:43:03,399
they should take the wife's family name.

666
00:43:03,840 --> 00:43:05,239
Not necessary.

667
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:06,639
We'll have several—

668
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:07,759
some can take each surname.

669
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:12,839
Continue reading!

670
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:14,119
The most important part—

671
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:18,239
the live-in husband shall remember: the wife holds authority.

672
00:43:18,240 --> 00:43:20,119
The woman is head of the household.

673
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:21,279
The husband answers to the wife in all things.

674
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:22,959
No need.

675
00:43:23,480 --> 00:43:25,479
No, no need for all of that.

676
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:27,639
From this day forth,

677
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:29,639
the husband shall heed the wife in all matters.

678
00:43:30,280 --> 00:43:31,159
And comply without exception.

679
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:35,279
In the future,

680
00:43:35,920 --> 00:43:37,079
we shall discuss things together

681
00:43:37,160 --> 00:43:38,039
and decide together.

682
00:43:38,840 --> 00:43:39,399
Good.

683
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:45,199
Then what are we waiting for?

684
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:46,479
Escort the newlyweds to the bridal chamber!

685
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:49,079
Come, come!

686
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:49,799
Yan Zheng!

687
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:51,599
Let's go, Yan Zheng!

688
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:57,319
The bride is here to toast everyone!

689
00:43:57,720 --> 00:44:01,199
Thank you, thank you, everyone!

690
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:02,039
Congratulations!

691
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:06,759
The new bride is toasting us!

692
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:08,079
Changyu, congratulations!

693
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:11,039
Everyone has worked so hard today.

694
00:44:11,040 --> 00:44:12,799
Eat and drink your fill!

695
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:14,559
Toast the bride!

696
00:44:16,040 --> 00:44:16,799
Come, come!

697
00:45:00,680 --> 00:45:02,079
Everyone eat and drink well!

698
00:45:03,600 --> 00:45:05,759
My girl.

699
00:45:06,440 --> 00:45:07,199
Uncle Wang.

700
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:08,439
Forgive me.

701
00:45:08,720 --> 00:45:09,239
I arrived late.

702
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:10,719
How could you only just arrive?

703
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:12,199
Uncle—

704
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:14,479
let me pour myself a penalty cup first.

705
00:45:17,360 --> 00:45:18,199
Hurry, hurry!

706
00:45:21,440 --> 00:45:22,519
These past days

707
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:23,999
have been hard on you.

708
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:26,119
I've seen it all.

709
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:27,879
I was your father's old friend.

710
00:45:28,120 --> 00:45:29,199
From now on,

711
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:31,319
think of me as family.

712
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:34,039
Old Zhao over there counts as the other half.

713
00:45:37,360 --> 00:45:39,319
My only wish for you

714
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,039
is that your days grow sweeter,

715
00:45:42,320 --> 00:45:44,119
your paths grow wider,

716
00:45:44,440 --> 00:45:45,439
your marriage harmonious,

717
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:46,319
your love enduring.

718
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:46,959
Good.

719
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:48,079
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

720
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:49,399
A toast!

721
00:46:00,880 --> 00:46:02,159
Thank you all today.

722
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:04,039
Don't mention it.

723
00:46:04,040 --> 00:46:05,519
She looks so beautiful.

724
00:46:05,520 --> 00:46:06,559
You've worked hard today, Changyu.

725
00:46:06,560 --> 00:46:07,639
Go rest.

726
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:08,239
Good.

727
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:08,879
Be careful on your way.

728
00:46:08,880 --> 00:46:09,999
Congratulations, Changyu.

729
00:46:10,080 --> 00:46:11,679
Beautiful—get some rest.

730
00:46:11,680 --> 00:46:12,519
Sleep well.

731
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:23,759
What do you think you're doing?

732
00:46:24,320 --> 00:46:25,119
I'm washing the bowls.

733
00:46:25,200 --> 00:46:25,839
Wait—

734
00:46:26,920 --> 00:46:28,799
you don't need to do that.

735
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:38,799
I don't need to?

736
00:46:38,960 --> 00:46:40,599
He doesn't need to—with those injuries.

737
00:46:40,640 --> 00:46:42,319
There'll be plenty of use for him later.

738
00:46:42,400 --> 00:46:43,599
Hurry back to the bridal chamber!

739
00:46:43,920 --> 00:46:45,279
Let me finish washing first.

740
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:46,399
You leave the washing!

741
00:46:47,160 --> 00:46:48,879
Changyu! Don't just stand there!

742
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:54,199
Changyu! Changyu!

743
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:55,399
Go up to your room.

744
00:46:55,560 --> 00:46:58,399
A wedding night is worth a thousand gold.

745
00:47:03,840 --> 00:47:04,639
All right, all right!

746
00:47:04,640 --> 00:47:05,559
Go, go, go.

747
00:47:13,160 --> 00:47:13,559
Wait.

748
00:47:17,840 --> 00:47:18,799
Forgive me.

749
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:22,839
I've lived alone for so long—

750
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:24,239
I keep forgetting there's a man in the house now.
